{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-jsx","path":"/how-to-remove-a-specific-item-from-a-list-array-javascript","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1 id=\"how-to-remove-a-specific-item-from-a-list-array-in-javascript\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#how-to-remove-a-specific-item-from-a-list-array-in-javascript\" aria-label=\"how to remove a specific item from a list array in javascript permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How to remove a specific item from a list (array) in Javascript</h1>\n<p>Removing an element by value from an array is a very common task in day to day coding.\nJavascript Arays do not directly expose method to do this by element value, however this can easily be achieved using\nthe <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/splice\"><code class=\"language-text\">splice</code></a> method:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> vegetables <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">'Cabbage'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Turnip'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Radish'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Carrot'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>vegetables<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// [\"Cabbage\", \"Turnip\", \"Radish\", \"Carrot\"]</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Remove \"Radish\"</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> removedItem <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> vegetables<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">splice</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>vegetables<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">indexOf</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'Radish'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// this is how to remove an item</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>vegetables<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// [\"Cabbage\", \"Turnip\", \"Carrot\"]</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'Removed item:'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> removedItem<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Removed Item: Radish</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>The <code class=\"language-text\">splice</code> approach is the recommended way of removing an element in Javascript\n(See <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array#Description\">\"Common Operations\" on MDN</a>).</p>\n<p>The <code class=\"language-text\">splice</code> method changes the content of the array by removing (and/or replacing) elements in the array, at the given\nposition.\nThe first argument to <code class=\"language-text\">splice</code> is the position (0-based) of the first element to be removed, and the second argument\nis the number of elements to be removed from the array starting at that position. By setting <code class=\"language-text\">1</code> as the second argument, only the\nelement at the given position will be removed.</p>\n<p>An important thing to note is that this approach mutates the array.</p>\n<h2 id=\"remove-an-element-by-value-without-modifying-the-original-array\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#remove-an-element-by-value-without-modifying-the-original-array\" aria-label=\"remove an element by value without modifying the original array permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Remove an element by value without modifying the original array</h2>\n<p>To remove an element without modifying the original array, we can use <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/slice\"><code class=\"language-text\">slice</code></a>\nto slice the array into two sub-arrays and then concatenate them both into one array:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> vegetables <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">'Cabbage'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Turnip'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Radish'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Carrot'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> pos <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> vegetables<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">indexOf</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'Radish'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>  <span class=\"token comment\">// get the position of the element we want to remove</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> vegetablesNoRadish <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> vegetables<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">slice</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> pos<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">concat</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>vegetables<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">slice</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>pos <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>vegetablesNoRadish<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// [\"Cabbage\", \"Turnip\", \"Carrot\"]</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// The original array is unchanged</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>vegetables<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// [\"Cabbage\", \"Turnip\", \"Radish\", \"Carrot\"]</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"remove-all-elements-with-the-same-value-from-the-array\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#remove-all-elements-with-the-same-value-from-the-array\" aria-label=\"remove all elements with the same value from the array permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Remove all elements with the same value from the array</h2>\n<p>To remove all elements in the array that have the given value, we can use method <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/filter\"><code class=\"language-text\">filter</code></a>:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> vegetables <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">'Cabbage'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Turnip'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Radish'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Carrot'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Radish'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> vegetablesNoRadish <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> vegetables<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">filter</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">function</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">val</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> val <span class=\"token operator\">!==</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Radish'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>vegetablesNoRadish<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// [\"Cabbage\", \"Turnip\", \"Carrot\"]</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Using ECMA Script 6:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> vegetables <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">'Cabbage'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Turnip'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Radish'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Carrot'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Radish'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> vegetablesNoRadish <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> vegetables<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">filter</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">val</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> val <span class=\"token operator\">!==</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Radish'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\nconsole<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>vegetablesNoRadish<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// [\"Cabbage\", \"Turnip\", \"Carrot\"]</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>The approaches above work for most of the popular browsers and in NodeJS environments.</p>","timeToRead":2,"excerpt":"How to remove a specific item from a list (array) in Javascript Removing an element by value from an array is a very common task in day to…","frontmatter":{"title":"How to remove a specific item from a list (array) [Javascript]","date":"2020-05-12 20:57:13 +0200","categories":["javascript"],"tags":["javascript","es6","nodejs","array"],"description":null,"keywords":"javascript, es6, nodejs, array","author":"Pavle Jonoski","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","width":204,"height":132,"src":"/static/d8c14182a961200c4f88c50ed97c2437/02521/javascript.png","srcSet":"/static/d8c14182a961200c4f88c50ed97c2437/02521/javascript.png 1x"}}}},"fields":{"slug":"/how-to-remove-a-specific-item-from-a-list-array-javascript","date":"2020-05-12T18:57:13.000Z"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/how-to-remove-a-specific-item-from-a-list-array-javascript","nexttitle":"Pandas read files","nextslug":"/pandas-read-files","prevtitle":"Git delete a branch remotely","prevslug":"/git-delete-a-branch-remotely","tagList":["python","pandas","abstraction","OOP","Class","java","collection","API","Map","HashMap","LinkedHashMap","TreeMap","Python","cli","args","argparse","javascript","es6","beginner","codenewbie","Primary_key","implementation","Composite_key","language-support","localization","internationalization","linux","file permissions","Project Euler","Algortithms","SQL","database","commands","GO","Datatypes","Variab